definitions.definition: A renowned Old English alliterative poem, preserved in a single manuscript within the Nowell Codex , composed sometime between 975 and 1025 AD.
An Anglo-Saxon personal name , usually with reference to the hero of the poem, or to the poem itself.
examples: Beowulf is as great a hero as Sigmund.
